Marex Spectron Hires Wilson to Manage Commodities in Geneva

-- B y   A g n i e s z k a   T r o s z k i e w i c z
-- 
2011-09-14T14:06:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-14/marex-spectron-hires-wilson-to-manage-commodities-in-geneva-1-.html
Marex Spectron Group, a commodities
brokerage, hired  Thomas Wilson  to be the managing director of
Marex Financial Suisse SA, with a focus on  hedge funds .  Wilson will be based in Geneva and report to Gavin Prentice, the global head of sales, Prentice said in an e-mail.
He joins from Klesch & Co. in Geneva, where he was responsible
for the management of commodity portfolios.  He previously worked for companies including Natixis
Commodity Markets Ltd. and Goldman Sachs Group Inc., Marex
Spectron said in a statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Agnieszka Troszkiewicz in London at 
 atroszkiewic@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at  ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net  